<a name="BOXCOLORS">

<H1>BOXCOLORS
</H1>


<P>
<A name="index_35_6"></A> The <B>\BOXCOLORS</B> tag is used to change the background and foreground colors of text boxes used for example code.
</P>


<P>
<B>Syntax</B>
</P>


<P>
\BOXCOLORS{fg=<I>fgcolor</I> bg=<I>bgcolor</I>}
</P>


<P>
\BOXCOLORS{set=default}
</P>


<P>
<B>Options</B>
</P>

<DL>
<DT>
<B>fg</B></DT>
<DD>
This option specifies the foreground color
</DD>
<DT>
<B>bg</B></DT>
<DD>
This option specifies the background color
</DD>
<DT>
<B>set=default</B></DT>
<DD>
This option resets the colors to their original values.
</DD>
</DL>


<P>
<B>Body</B>
</P>


<P>
No body is allowed.
</P>


<P>
<B>Examples</B>
</P>


<TABLE BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=5 WIDTH=80%><TR><TD bgcolor="#e5e5e5"><PRE>
<FONT COLOR="#000000">
  \BOXCOLORS{fg=white bg=blue}

  \BOXCOLORS{bg=&quot;#AFBDCA&quot;}
</FONT></PRE></TD></TR></TABLE>


<P>

</P>


<TABLE BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=5 WIDTH=80%><TR><TD bgcolor="#AFBDCA"><PRE>
<FONT COLOR="#000000">
  This is a colored box ...
</FONT></PRE></TD></TR></TABLE>


